The devastated mother of a British backpacker killed in a car crash said she does not want to see her daughter's body as she does not want that to be her last memory.

Jade Fox, 22, was travelling through Fraser Island in Queensland when it is believed she fatally hit her head when the 4x4 vehicle she was in overturned at around 2pm on Friday.

She was travelling with seven other friends who all survived the crash with minor injuries.

