Ms Fox, from Maidstone in Kent posted an update on Facebook on the morning of her death. She said: 'Up early doors to travel Frazer Island for three days.'

Her father Chris has travelled to Australia to arrange the repatriation of her body. 

Speaking to the BBC, her mother Melanie, 46, said before heading to Australia, she asked her daughter to be careful: 'I always told her if anything happened to her I couldn't cope or with any of them and I said you need to look after yourself, but I couldn't stop her living her dream.

'Her dad says he wants to hold her and see her, I don't think he believes it, but I don't want to see her broken, I just want to remember her how she was.

'I've rarely seen her without a smile so I don't want that to be my last memory of her not smiling.'

